name: Seahawks
summary: The Seattle Seahawks kicked off their season with a 26-20 victory over the Denver Broncos, sparked by a strong running game. Russell Wilson is expected to lead the Seahawks offense when they face the Broncos, who will rely on Teddy Bridgewater at quarterback. The game will be available to watch on FOX, listen to on KIRO Radio 97.3 FM, or streamed live on NFL Game Pass, Amazon Prime Video, and fuboTV. The Seahawks have added two defenders, Kenneth Odumegwu and Quinton Bohanna, to their practice squad ahead of the season opener. Additionally, the team has unveiled "Bam C. Hawk" as their international mascot. Coach Ryan Grubb is eager to debut his new offensive scheme against the Broncos, while the Seahawks defense is determined to regain their physical edge under coordinator Mike Macdonald.

name: Texans
summary: In the NFL season opener, the Houston Texans upset the Indianapolis Colts 29-27, led by team captains including seven Texans. Despite defensive struggles, the Texans' newcomers, Diggs and Mixon, excelled in the win. The game featured a confusing clock runoff sequence that the NFL later clarified. The Texans' offense showed promise, but there are concerns that need to be addressed. Quarterback C.J. Stroud expressed satisfaction with the victory while emphasizing areas for improvement. Former Bengals player Joe Mixon declared his desire to surpass his previous team after finding a stronger fit with the Texans.

name: Dak Prescott
summary: Dak Prescott, the star quarterback for the Dallas Cowboys, has signed a record-breaking four-year contract extension worth $240 million, making him the highest-paid player in the NFL. The deal ensures Prescott will remain with the Cowboys through the 2026 season and guarantees him an average annual salary of $60 million, becoming the first player to reach such a high per-year earnings mark. This massive contract extension signifies the long-term commitment between the Cowboys and Prescott, acknowledging his impact on the team and the NFL as a whole.
